'''Arne Bergsgård''' (18 April 1886 &ndash; 18 June 1954) was a Norwegian historian and educator.<ref name=snl/><ref>[http://www.strindahistorielag.no/wiki/index.php?title=Arne_Bergsg%C3%A5rd ''Arne Bergsgård'' (WikiStrinda)]</ref>
==Biography== Arne Bergsgård was born in [[Vestre Slidre]] in [[Oppland]] and grew up in [[Vang, Oppland|Vang]], Norway. He was the son of Asle Bergsgård and Ingeborg Thune. He attended high school in [[Fredrikstad]], where he graduated in 1904. In 1910, he took his philological degree. He served as a teacher from 1911-1914 in [[Volda]] and 1914-22 at [[Stord]]. In 1922, he was appointed senior lecturer in history at the [[Norwegian College of General Sciences]] in [[Trondheim]]. He earned his [[dr.philos.]] degree in 1933, with a thesis on [[Ole Gabriel Gabrielsen Ueland|Ole Gabriel Ueland]] and in 1935, he became a professor. He was rector of the College from 1937 to 1953. He was a board member of [[Noregs Mållag]] from 1929 to 1936.<ref name=nbl/>
During the [[occupation of Norway by Nazi Germany]] he joined [[Norwegian resistance movement|the resistance movement]], editing the underground publication ''I krigstid''. He was a member of the post-war investigation committee, ''[[Undersøkelseskommisjonen av 1945]]'', where he wrote the appendix on the Norwegian Government's Foreign Policy up to April 1940.<ref>{{cite book|chapter=Utenrikspolitikken til april 1940 |first=Arne|last=Bergsgård|title=Innstilling fra Undersøkelseskommisjonen av 1945. Bilag |volume=1 |pages=117&ndash;264 |year=1947 |publisher=Aschehoug |location=Oslo|language=Norwegian}}</ref>
As a historian, he concentrated largely on the 19th Century, primarily the emergence of the Norwegian national identity. He was a member of [[Royal Norwegian Society of Sciences and Letters]] from 1926 and the [[Norwegian Academy of Science and Letters]] from 1938. He was decorated Knight, First Class of the [[Order of St. Olav]] in 1950.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Arne Bergsgård |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Arne_Bergsgård |language=Norwegian | accessdate=18 April 2011 }}</ref><ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Arne Bergsgård |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Anders |last=Kirkhusmo |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Arne_Bergsgård/utdypning |language=Norwegian|accessdate=18 April 2011}}</ref> <ref>[http://www.allkunne.no/default.aspx?menu=353&id=617 ''Arne Bergsgård'' (Allkunne AS)]</ref> <ref>[http://www.denstoredanske.dk/Special:Tags?tag=Arne+Bergsg%C3%A5rd ''Arne Bergsgård'' (Den Store Danske)]</ref>
