'''Henri Bourde de La Rogerie''' (8 April 1873, [[Ernée]] – 31 January 1949, [[Rennes]]) was a [[France|French]] [[archivist]] and historian of [[Brittany]].
He studied at the college in [[Saint-Lô]], then received his law degree from the [[University of Caen]] and his diploma as an archivist-paleographer at the [[École Nationale des Chartes|École des Chartes]] (1895). During his career, he worked as an archivist in the departments of [[Finistère]] (1897–1912) and [[Ille-et-Villaine]] (1912–34).<ref>[http://biblcham.umoncton.ca/cal/secteurs/1/documents/1423 Henri Bourde de la Rogerie] Collections acadiennes en ligne</ref><ref>[http://www.persee.fr/doc/bec_0373-6237_1950_num_108_1_460281 Henri Bourde de la Rogerie] Persée (necrology)</ref><ref name=SS>[http://cths.fr/an/prosopo.php?id=1705 Bourde de La Rogerie, Henri Francois Marie Joseph] Sociétés savantes de France</ref>
He served as president of the Société archéologique d'Ille-et-Vilaine and the Société d'histoire et d'archéologie de Bretagne.<ref name=SS/>
== Selected works == * ''Correspondance de Guillaume Charrier, abbé de Sainte-Croix de Quimperlé'' (as editor, 1901) &ndash; Correspondence of Guillaume Charrier, abbot of Sainte-Croix de [[Quimperlé]]. * ''Les Bretons dans la Louisiane française. Le Chevalier de Kerlérec'', (1904) &ndash; The Bretons in [[French Louisiana]]; the [[Louis Billouart|Chevalier de Kerlérec]]. * ''Notice sur un recueil de plans d'édifices construits par les architectes de la Compagnie de Jésus, 1607-1672'', (1904) &ndash; About a collection of building plans constructed by architects of the [[Society of Jesus]] from 1607 to 1672. * ''Les Voyageurs en Bretagne. Le Voyage de Mignot de Montigny en Bretagne en 1752'' &ndash; Voyagers in Brittany; the voyage of [[Étienne Mignot de Montigny|Mignot de Montigny]] in Brittany in 1752. * ''Les fondations de villes et de bourgs en Bretagne du XIe au XIIIe siècle'', (1928) &ndash; Religious foundations in the towns of Brittany in the 17th and 18th centuries. * ''Les Bretons aux Iles de France et de Bourbon'', (1934) &ndash; Bretons in [[Mauritius]] and [[Réunion]]. * ''Les Abbayes cisterciennes de Bretagne en 1600'', (1936) &ndash; [[Cistercian]] abbeys of Brittany in 1600.<ref>[http://data.bnf.fr/12592286/henri_bourde_de_la_rogerie/ Henri Bourde de La Rogerie (1873-1949)] data.bnf.fr.</ref>
