== 21st century == {| class="wikitable" width="100%" ! style="width:6%" | Year || style="width:10%" | Date || Event |- | 2003 || 6 July || ''[[Mexican legislative election, 2003]]'': The [[Institutional Revolutionary Party|PRI]] won a plurality of seats in the [[Chamber of Deputies (Mexico)|Chamber of Deputies]]. |- | rowspan="2" valign="top" | 2006 || 2 July || ''[[Mexican general election, 2006]]'': [[Felipe Calderón]] of the [[National Action Party (Mexico)|National Action Party (PAN)]] won the [[President of Mexico|presidency]] with 36% of the vote. The PAN won a plurality of seats in the [[Chamber of Deputies (Mexico)|Chamber of Deputies]]. |- | 30 July || [[Andrés Manuel López Obrador]] of the [[Party of the Democratic Revolution|PRD]] led hundreds of thousands in a protest against the election results at [[Zócalo]] in Mexico City. |- | 2009 || 5 July || ''[[Mexican legislative election, 2009]]'': The [[Institutional Revolutionary Party|PRI]] won a plurality of seats in the [[Chamber of Deputies (Mexico)|Chamber of Deputies]]. |- | 2012 || 1 July || ''[[Mexican general election, 2012]]'': [[Enrique Peña Nieto]] of the [[Institutional Revolutionary Party|PRI]] won the [[President of Mexico|presidency]] with 39% of the vote. The PRI won a plurality of seats in the [[Chamber of Deputies (Mexico)|Chamber of Deputies]]. |}
